                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#48r"/>
                           <desc type="Exhortation">Liturgical directives</desc>
                           <note>
                              The note containes directives on the readings for the office of the sixth hour, the third hour and the hour of the rest. 
                              It starts as follows: <q xml:lang="gez">
                                 <choice>
                                    <sic>በ፯፡</sic>
                                    <corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">በ፮፡</corr>
                                 </choice> 
                                 
                                    <sic>ስዓት፡</sic>
                                  መዝሙር። ዘ፶። <gap reason="omitted" extent="unknown" resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices"/> ዘ፹፬። 
                                 
                                    <sic>ወትዓብዮ።</sic>
                                  ወዓንቀፀ፡ ብርሃን። 
                                    <sic>ወንጌል፡</sic>
                                  ማቴዎስ። ወሶበ፡ ርእየ። ወ፵፩፡ ኪርያላሶን። ወአቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት።
                              </q>.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#48v"/>
                           <desc type="Exhortation">Prayer for each hour</desc>
                           <note>
                              The prayer begins as follows: <q xml:lang="gez">ወዘንተ፡ ትብል፡ ለለኵሉ፡ 
                                    <sic>ስዓት።</sic>
                                  ኦዘበ፡ ኵሉ፡ 
                                    <sic>ጌዜ፡</sic>
                                  
                              ወሰዓት፡ በሰማይ፡ ወበምድር፡ ዘይሰግዱ፡ ሎቱ፡ ወይሴባሕ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ አምላክነ፡</q>, and terminates as follows: <q xml:lang="gez">እስመ፡ አንተ፡ ቡሩክ፡ ወለከ፡ ስብሓት፡ ለዓለመ፡ 
                                 ዓለም፡ አሜን።</q>.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#48v"/>
                           <desc>Untitled prayer</desc>
                           <note>The prayer begins as follows: <q xml:lang="gez">ኦዘትፌንዎ፡ ለብርሃን፡ 
                                    <sic>ወይሐውር፡</sic>
                                  ዘያሠርቅ፡ 
                                    <sic>ጸሐይ፡</sic>
                                  
                              ላዕለ፡ ሔራን፡ ወላዕለ፡ 
                                    <sic>አኩያን።</sic>
                                 
                              </q>. It terminates abruptly due to material loss.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>The shelfmark of the Vatican Library <q xml:lang="la">Vat. | 27 | aethiop.</q> is written on the cover, together with the coat of 
                              arms of pope <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7893PiusIX">Pius IX</persName> and the librarian <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11256PitraGB">Giovanni Battista Pitra</persName>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <locus target="#1r"/>
                           <desc>The title of the book <q xml:lang="la">Psalterium Abasinu<supplied reason="explanation">m</supplied> Chaldaeum sive 
                              Aethiopicum, cum Precationib<supplied reason="explanation">us</supplied> Mosis et veteris testamenti sanctorum hominu<supplied reason="explanation">m</supplied>
                              </q> 
                              is written in a <date>17th-century</date> hand in the lower margin of the leaf. 
                              Two illegible words are written below the title in a different hand.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>The <foreign xml:lang="gez">zǝyā</foreign>-sign and the titles of the psalms referring to Christ and the Churhc have been added in a later hand in the left and in the upper margin, resepctively. 
                           The titles are partly lost due to the intervention of a later conservator.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
